Indian Equities: Hindustan Dorr, Kingfisher Airlines, Ranbaxy

-- B y   H e m a l   S a v a i
-- 
2011-12-02T04:25:37Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-02/indian-equities-hindustan-dorr-kingfisher-airlines-ranbaxy.html
Shares of the following companies had
 unusual (SENSEX)  moves in  Indian trading. (BSE100)  Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 9:36 a.m. local time.  The BSE India Sensitive Index, or Sensex, slid 0.2 percent
to 16,457.17. The  BSE 200 Index (BSE200)  fell 0.1 percent to 1,988.20.  Hindustan Dorr-Oliver Ltd. (HDOR)   advanced 1.4 percent
to 24.65 rupees. The Indian engineering company has won orders
valued at 2.4 billion rupees ($46.7 million), Executive Director
S.C. Sekaran said. The orders came from ACC Ltd., NMDC Ltd. and
Nuclear Power Corp. of India, Sekaran said in an interview.  Kingfisher Airlines Ltd. (KAIR)   lost 4 percent to 22.9
rupees, set for the biggest drop in three weeks. Mumbai
International Airport Pvt. said it would suspend credit to the
airline after a check issued by the carrier for airport services
bounced, the Press Trust of India reported, citing an official
it didn’t identify.  Ranbaxy Laboratories Ltd. (RBXY)   sank 1 percent to 439
rupees after Israel’s Teva Pharmaceutical Industries Ltd. said
that it isn’t supplying ingredients to the Indian company to
make Lipitor copies in the U.S.  Ranbaxy said yesterday that it will pay a portion of
profits from Lipitor sales for six months to Teva, without
giving any details of the agreement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Hemal Savai in Mumbai at  at
 hsavai@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Darren Boey at 
 dboey@bloomberg.net . 